                  ================================================================
                          Primary Key & Composite Primary key in DB
                  ================================================================

==> Primary key is a constraint to maintain unique records in the table.

Primary key = UNIQUE + NOT NULL

==> If we try to insert duplicate value in primary key column value then we will get UniqueConstraintException..
==> We should not ask end users to enter value for PK column because users may enter duplicate value.
==> To generate value for PK(primary key) column we will use GENERATOR concept.


                ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ MYSQL ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
              
                        AUTO/SEQUENCE/TABLE ===> Behaviour is same
                        IDENTITY ====> Will use AUTO_INCREMENT to generate value for Primary key column value
Note: MYSQL will not support Sequences.
                        
               ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ Oracle DB ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
              
                    AUTO     ==> Sequence to generate primary key value (default sequence name: hibernate_sequence) 
                    SEQUENCE ==> We can configure our own sequence to generate PK value like below

Note: Oracle DB will not support for AUTO_INCREMENT.

                            create sequence pid_seq
                            start with 1000
                            increment by 1;

TABLE ==> New table will be create to maintain primary column values

=================================CONFIGURING COSTUME SEQUENCE TO GENERATE PK VALUE =================================================

==> First we need to create sequence in db like below 

                            create sequence pid_seq
                            start with 1000
                            increment by 1;

==> Configure Custom Sequence in Enity class like below 

@Id
@SequenceGenerator(name = "pid", sequenceName = "pid_seq")
@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE,generator = "pid")
private Integer productId;







